I would like to try and schedule a convenient time to discuss with you the
role/scope of the PX Participants Committee.  Reliant has been concerned
for some time about the continued life line of the PX and this committee
and the additional layer of expenses that are being incurred (see BDO's
recent analysis of the PX budget for example).  It seems to me that the
sole role of the PX and the committee (other than with respect to
litigation that has already commenced such as the commandeering litigation)
aught to be limited to (i) record/data retention and (ii) finalizing
accounting issues so that each participant has a certification of how much
it is owed by each defaulting IOU.  The PX seems to have lost its "pass
through" nature, which is critical to each participant being able to asset
its claims directly.   I am particularly concerned that the committee,
through its professionals is beginning to have a life of its own.

It would be useful to have this discussion prior to the committee meeting
tomorrow afternoon.  Are you available after 10 a.m. central time tomorrow
to discuss?

Sheryl Gussett
Senior Counsel
Reliant Resources, Inc.
713-207-8538
713-207-0159 (fax)
sheryl_gussett@reliantenergy.com

