We will be running a TD Williamson Caliper tool in the mainline in Section 8 and 7 the week of August 20th.  The following week we will be running the tool in both the mainline and loopline in section 5.  The proposed schedule is as follow:

Monday - 8-20-01 - Safety and tailgate meeting - 1:00/PM MDT - at Station 8 (Corona) - set out AGM's
Tuesday - 8-21-01 - Run tool from Sta. 8 to Sta. 7 (Section 8 - Mainline) - pick up AGM's
Wednesday - 8-22-01 - Retrieve data and set pig up for next run - at Station 7 (Mountainair) - set out AGM's
Thursday - 8-23-01 - Run tool from Sta. 7 to Sta. 6  (Section 7 - Mainline) - pick up AGM's
Friday - 8-24-01 - Retrieve data and set pig up for next week in Gallup - at Station 6 (Laguna) - travel home
Monday - 8-27-01 - Safety and tailgate meeting - 1:00/PM MDT - at Station 5 (Thoreau) - set out AGM's
Tuesday - 8-28-01 - Run tool in Loopline to Sta. 4 (Section 5) - pick up AGM's 
Wednesday - 8-29-01 - Retrieve data and set pig up for next run - at Station 4 (Klagetoh - Haul pig to Sta. 5 - set out AGM's
Thursday - 8-30-01 - Run tool in Mainline from Sta. 5 to Sta. 4 (Section 5) - pick up AGM's
Friday - 8-31-01 - Retrieve data from pig - at Station 4 (Klagetoh) - travel home

Cleaning pigs are being run in Section 7 & 8 as gas flows allow.  Cleaning pigs will be ran in Section 5 during the week of Aug. 20th.  

Gallup - please notify Gary Choquette before and after each cleaning run and caliper run in Sect. 5 so he can check efficiencies.

Teams, please let me know who on your teams will be available for these caliper runs so I can set up support help as needed.  I know that Gallup will need 2 support people the week of Aug. 27th.

During the week of Sept. 10th there will be a TD Williamson representative on site to determine if Sections 7 & 8 are clean enough to smart pig.  Teams Roswell, Mountainair and Laguna will need to run the cleaning pigs until acceptably clean.  The smart pig runs in Section 7 & 8 is scheduled for the week of Sept. 17th.  I will send another e-mail dealing with the smart pig.

Following are directions to locations:

Sta. 8 (Corona)
From Corona, NM - Head East on Hwy. 247 for 18 mile, turn right (South) at TW sign.  Continue on this dirt road for 15miles.  Station is on the left (East) side of the road.
From Roswell, NM - Head North on Hwy. 285 for 57 miles.  Turn left (West) on Hwy. 247  for 34 miles.  Turn left (South) at TW sign, and follow directions above.

Sta. 7 (Mountainair)
From Mountainair, NM - Head South on Hwy. 55 for 11.7 miles.  Hwy. 55 turns left (East) at this point and County Road goes straight.  Take the county road which is gravel and follow main gravel road for 10.8 miles to Compressor Station.

Sta. 6 (Laguna)
From Albuquerque, NM - Head West on I-40 and take exit 114.  Head into Laguna, NM, go 1 mile West on old Hwy. 66.  Turn left (South) on first paved road, then turn right (West) on first paved road for .2 miles.  Turn left (South) at cattle guard for 1 mile passing the ball park.  Turn left (Southeast) on the first road past the bridge and go under I-40.  Stay on this road until you get to the station.  

Station 5 (Thoreau)
From Gallup, NM - Head East on I-40 and take Exit 44 at Thoreau, NM.  Turn left (North) onto Hwy. 371.  Continue on the Hwy. for .7 miles and take the 1st road to the left (West) after the bridge that crosses over the RR track.  Follow this road to the stop sign. At the stop sign make a right (North) and follow the road 1.7 miles staying to the right at the dirt road.  the station is on the right side.

Sta. 4 (Klagetoh)
From Chambers, AZ at Exit 333 on I-40:  Head North on 191 toward Ganado, AZ.  Go 2 miles past Klagetoh, AZ and turn right (East) on Transwestern Road (paved).  Follow this road to the end and the station.

