We just got off the phone with Alstom at 8:15 AM mountain time. John Manson is their service manager (412-967-7165). They are flying a motor specialist in from England, but he will not arrive until 7:00 PM Friday. At the present time Alstom is mobilizing IRS from Farmington, New Mexico to assist with the removal of the motor. The motor weighs nearly 35 tons, so permits, a crane and roof removal will be required. They plan to truck the motor back to Farmington for further analysis. They will then determine the repair process. I have set up a conference call for 1:00 PM Central time today, to allow everyone the opportunity to voice any concerns and get the latest updates from John and Alstom. The conference number is 877-795-3687 access code 691205.  I welcome all help and participation.  Rick

 
